Programming language vs Technology vs Framework
-----------------------------------------------
Q. What is a programming language ?
-> Programming language contains set of programs/Set of Instructions.
     Ex: c,c++, java
-> Every programming language will follow set of Syntaxes/Rules
-> Using programming language we can develop
   Application /Tools/ Softwares/Technologies/  Framework

What is technology ?
---------------------
Technology is a software which is developed by using Programming Languages.
  Ex: Servelts,JSP,JDBC
-> Technologies are used to simplify our task.
-> By using   Technologies we can develop several types of applications.

What is Framework ?
-------------------
-> To overcome the loop holes of Technologies Framework came into picture.
-> Framework is a semi developed software.
-> Framework provides common logic required for application development.
    Ex.
        1) Capture form data
        2) Validate form data
        3)Create Connection pool
        4) DB connection pool

-> Framework provides Re-usable componenets.
-> For example, Every java developer should write below lines of code to perform DB operations.
    class.forName("");
    DM.getConn("");
    createStatement();
    executeQuery()
    process ResultSet
    close connection
Note: If we write same code for multiple times then it is called Boiler plate code/Redundent Code.
--> To avoid duplicate code /common logics in project Framework came into picture.

      project = Common logics + Bussiness logics
-> Framework provides common logics required for the project so that we can focus only on bussiness logic development.
-> Frameworks will improve developers productivity.(we can do more work in less time ).
    Ex:
        Hibernate, spring,WCF,Django, Flask, Lightening etc.  


              Core java => programming
              JDBC + servlets + JSP =>  Technology
              Hibernate + strtus + Spring + Spring Boot ===> Frameworks
